snippet.textDisplay: As a 62 Yr young white male who is training for his 10th Ironman Triathlon in Nov , on Jan 5th 1988 my 1st favorite Basketball player died , Pete Maravich, hard work , thousands of hrs training  , leaving 2 young sons behind , now Jan 26th 2020 a new generation , new player, but again hard work , leaving young children behind . When I am on my indoor bike doing long tough workouts, will be watching video's of Kobe, when my 62 yr body is tired , or its raining outside and run workout is planned , will dress for it . I wish I had the relationships with my kids as Kobe  did , hopefully before I die will have that, but even a 62 yr white male can cry over a inspiring 41 black male as a son , we still have a chance as human beings . White old Mamba not out yet .
